    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_7aESZrg5i4gIDe2I-1", "label": "FAQ Title", "default": "<h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_9eTXhF2Jl59s8a6I-1", "label": "FAQ Subtitle", "default": "<p>Everything you need to know about our camera repair service. Can't find your answer? Reach out directly.</p>" },
    { "type": "url", "id": "url_hkfu6CK8SSCaCMoo-1", "label": "Contact Us Button URL" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_suzeb1nmUompX5cX-1", "label": "Contact Button Text", "default": "<p>Contact Us</p>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_yPOfQDQyudoffbEH-1", "label": "FAQ Q1", "default": "<h4>What is the bench fee and is it refundable?</h4>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_DyX1AepcieaXngSX-1", "label": "FAQ A1", "default": "<p>The bench fee is a non-refundable inspection charge that covers our technician's time to thoroughly assess your camera. This fee is applied toward your final repair cost if you proceed with the repair.</p>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_2uvk73piGaJVfSA1-1", "label": "FAQ Q2", "default": "<h4>How long will my repair take?</h4>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_ENPmwIUdsO9w8ai3-1", "label": "FAQ A2", "default": "<p>Standard repair turnaround is 2–4 weeks from when we receive your camera. Complex repairs or situations requiring special parts may take longer.</p>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_m9G2IMZMMGgH3J3w-1", "label": "FAQ Q3", "default": "<h4>What cameras do you repair?</h4>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_1YqXpD4kvhmSlv9K-1", "label": "FAQ A3", "default": "<p>We specialize in 35mm and medium format film cameras including Canon, Nikon, Pentax, Olympus, Minolta, Contax, Leica, Hasselblad, Mamiya, Bronica, Rolleiflex, Yashica, and many more.</p>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_JUKnHXd2MfaYQ4lL-1", "label": "FAQ Q4", "default": "<h4>Do you repair Polaroid cameras?</h4>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_nKyOLcNCxQ9BU6Lx-1", "label": "FAQ A4", "default": "<p>Polaroid cameras require specialized service. Please visit our dedicated Polaroid Repairs page for information on instant camera repair options and pricing.</p>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_9SpfQZ8nomRE73wp-1", "label": "FAQ Q5", "default": "<h4>How should I pack my camera for shipping?</h4>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_Ek5DbpeAU9rLi2mh-1", "label": "FAQ A5", "default": "<p>Wrap your camera in bubble wrap or foam and place it in a sturdy box with additional packing material. Remove batteries and any detachable lenses.</p>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_ReexIItutqMaLTuP-1", "label": "FAQ Q6", "default": "<h4>Will I receive a quote before any work is done?</h4>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_U5chG9FSxzdJdnk9-1", "label": "FAQ A6", "default": "<p>Absolutely. After the bench inspection, we'll contact you with a detailed quote. No repair work proceeds until you approve the estimate.</p>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_YIEerFC852DhgYeL-1", "label": "FAQ Q7", "default": "<h4>What payment methods do you accept?</h4>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_Xqgk9OZXuw21n0iY-1", "label": "FAQ A7", "default": "<p>We accept all major credit cards, PayPal, and Shop Pay. The bench fee is collected when you submit your repair request.</p>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_QNSMFgbyON2JQ9sv-1", "label": "FAQ Q8", "default": "<h4>Can I drop off my camera in person?</h4>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_FAZaZxa8kpRb1gbS-1", "label": "FAQ A8", "default": "<p>Yes! Submit your repair request online first, then drop off your camera at 855 Grand St, Brooklyn any day we are open.</p>" },
    { "type": "header", "content": "Shipping Section" },
    { "type": "image_picker", "id": "image_ZGC0Rvijr6dtTfOn-1", "label": "Shipping Image" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_B6eNUe5cX9LOchif-1", "label": "Shipping Title", "default": "<h3>Secure Shipping &amp; Handling</h3>" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "text_9RZitkmjBUPjFcoq-1", "label": "Shipping Body", "default": "<p>Getting your camera to us has never been easier. Simply buy a label on our portal and get it instantly.</p><p>Your camera is handled with the utmost care throughout the repair process. We photograph every camera upon arrival to document its condition. Return shipping options include USPS Priority, UPS Ground, or expedited services. All shipments are fully insured for your peace of mind.</p>" },
